WHEN RONALD WAS A KID HE THOUGHT HE WAS RICK.
ONE NIGHT AT DINNER HE SAID, "I'M SO GLAD WE'RE RICH.
HIS DAD ALMOST CHOKED AND TOLD HIM THAT THEY WERE NOT RICH THEY WERE POOR.
HIS DAD GOT A JOB AS THE CUSTODIAN OF THE LIBRARY.
RONALD HAD ACCESS TO ALL OF THE BOOKS IN THE LIBRARY.
ANY TIME HE HAD A QUESTION ABOUT SOMETHING HE COULD GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY AND FIND A BOOK ABOUT IT.
AT FIRST RONALD WAS ASHAMED OF WHERE HE LIVED.
RONALD WAS THE FIRST OF HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE FROM HIGH SCHOOL AND GO TO COLLEGE.
HE READ LOTS OF BOOK AND DEVELOPED A THIRST FOR KNOWLEDGE.
WHEN RONALD GREW UP HE BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE.
WHEN HE SHOWED HIS DAD THE DOOR TO HIS CLASSROOM WITH HIS NAME ON IT HIS DAD JUST NODDED BUT HE COULD TELL HE WAS HAPPY BY THE LOOK IN HIS EYE.
HIS DAD WANTED HIM TO SUCCEED IN LIFE.
WHEN RONALD WAS A BOY HE THOUGHT THEY WERE RICH.
HE WAS HAVING DINNER WITH HIS FAMILY AND HE SAID HOW HAPPY HE WAS THAT THEY WERE RICH.
HIS FATHER NEARLY CHOKED AND TOLD HIM THAT THEY WERE POOR.
HIS FATHER BECAME THE CUSTODIAN OF THE LIBRARY.
EVERYWHERE YOU LOOKED IN THE LIBRARY WAS WAXED.
HE EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE BOOKCASES.
WHEN YOU LOOKED AT THE TOP OF THE BOOKCASES THEY GLEAMED.
RONALD WAS ASHAMED OF WHERE THEY LIVED BECAUSE NO ONE ELSE LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
DURING THE DAY HE HAD TO BE QUIET BUT AT NIGHT HE WAS THE ONLY KID THERE AND HE COULD RUN AND YELL ALL HE WANTED.
HE DEVELOPED A LOVE FOR READING AND KNOWLEDGE.
IF HE HAD A QUESTION ABOUT SOMETHING HE COULD GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY AND READ ABOUT IT.
HE WOULD READ UNTIL LATE IN THE NIGHT.
WHEN HE GREW UP HE BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE.
HE SHOWED HIS DAD THE DOOR TO HIS CLASSROOM THAT HAD HIS NAME ON IT.
HIS DAD WAS QUIET BUT RONALD COULD TELL THAT HE WAS PROUD.
